Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces; place in a #medium pot{} with enough
salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender,
~{10-12%minutes}.

Reserve 1 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to #pot.
Keep covered off heat until ready to mash in Step 4.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}. Season
with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, core, and thinly slice @Apple{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice
@Onion{1}. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{2%clove}.

Pat chicken dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @Dried Thyme{1%teaspoon},
half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later), @Salt{}, and
@Pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} and cook until browned and cooked through,
~{3-5%minutes} per side. TIP: Reduce heat if browning too quickly.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan and let cool
slightly.

> Swap in pork for chicken. Cook until browned and cooked through, 4-6 minutes
> per side.

While chicken cooks, to pot with potatoes, add @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon} and
@Butter{2%TBSP} (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth
and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Taste and
season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Keep covered until ready to serve.

Heat @Butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in
pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add apple, onion, remaining Fry Seasoning,
@sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4), @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until
softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add garlic, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, and @water{1/2%cup} (1 cup for 4).
Simmer until saucy and slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. TIP: If sauce seems
too thick, stir in splashes of water as needed.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide roasted carrots and mashed potatoes between shallow #bowls{} in separate
sections. Top mashed potatoes with chicken. Spoon apple and onion sauce over
chicken. Serve.

> Slice pork crosswise if using pork instead of chicken.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.